    "body": "While I'm down for rock-solid solutions for the critical stuff, I'd like to avoid a painful deploy process for the less critical things:\r\n\r\n* Announcements - Definitely don't want to start pointing people towards some scam ICO, so yeah, this would be a good choice for that.\r\n* Node list - I don't feel like a malicious node does a terrible amount of damage, and could be caught pretty fast. Perhaps we hard-code the default node, but allow the list to be loaded dynamically to mitigate any damage?\r\n* Gas defaults - Worst it could do is make unobservant people overpay / fail to transact. Not a big deal.\r\n* Network tokens - Since all you're sending is data, not ETH, I don't think this can be used maliciously? Someone correct me if I'm wrong.\r\n* Contract ABIs - Definitely a danger zone here, since someone could change the contract address, and would be pretty subtle.",
